nexml.^ot:comment:
Note: I (Nick Matzke) am the author of the digitized Newick file, not the original published phylogenies of Wang and Tedford (obviously).

Time tree of fossil and living Canidae, mostly from North America. Manually digitized by Nick Matzke using TreeRogue (https://stat.ethz.ch/pipermail/r-sig-phylo/2010-October/000816.html) from the summary phylogenies of the 3 monographs published by Wang & Tedford.

Tedford, Richard H.; Wang, Xiaoming; Taylor, Beryl E. (2009). Phylogenetic systematics of the North American fossil Caninae (Carnivora, Canidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, no. 325. http://hdl.handle.net/2246/5999

Wang, Xiaoming; Tedford, Richard H.; Taylor, Beryl E. (1999). Phylogenetic systematics of the Borophaginae (Carnivora, Canidae). Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, no. 243. http://hdl.handle.net/2246/1588

Wang, Xiaoming (1994). Phylogenetic systematics of the Hesperocyoninae (Carnivora, Canidae). Bulletin of the  American Museum of Natural History, no. 221. http://hdl.handle.net/2246/829

Digitization was done with TreeRogue and GraphClick, from the summary phylogeny figures of Wang & Tedford. Various judgement calls were required; my goal was to preserve the authors' depiction of relationships and divergence times.
